    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-04T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-04T04:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Republic of China</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_RANKINJL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-04T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 4, 1953—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>147. <persName corresp="#p_TSIANGTF1">T. F. Tsiang</persName> has indicated to
                    Chinese Foreign Ministry his alarm over <persName corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1">Mme.
                        Pandit</persName>’s candidacy for President <gloss target="#t_UNGA1"
                        >UNGA</gloss>.<note n="1" xml:id="d462fn1">For documentation on this matter
                        and other elections to <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> organs, see <ref
                            target="#pg_414">pp. 414</ref> ff.</note> Vice Minister Hu told me
                    Chinese Government understands how desire gratify India after latter’s
                    (rejection from political conference on Korea might lead US to vote for
                        <persName corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1">Mme. Pandit</persName> but hopes US will
                    not endeavor line up additional support for her.</p>
                <p>Hu also asked me to express Chinese Government’s belief that <persName
                        corresp="#p_PANDITMVL1">Mme. Pandit</persName> selection would have most
                    serious effect on its interests particularly in connection president’s influence
                    over credentials committee.</p>
                <p>While appreciating good support in UNO received from US to date Hu expressed hope
                    that in due course Department might instruct US delegation to concert with
                    Chinese delegation in finding definitive formula for Chinese representation in
                    place of successive postponements.</p>
                <p>In above connection see my despatch 96, August 24.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RANKINJL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rankin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
